  <abstract>This episode opens with an interview with two members of the Canadian Hispanic Congress, who discuss some of their future plans for the Hispanic community in Canada. The next segment features part of the Victor Jara Festival. Specifically, a performance of several traditional Northern Chilean folk dances. Finally, the last segment focusses on transition to democracy in Latin America and features numerous interviews with Brazilian and Chilean citizens regarding their opinions on life under authoritarian governments.</abstract>
